NAME
    Acme::CPANModules::ColorEnv - Modules that observe environment variable
    (other than NO_COLOR/COLOR) to disable/enable colored output

VERSION
    This document describes version 0.001 of Acme::CPANModules::ColorEnv
    (from Perl distribution Acme-CPANModules-ColorEnv), released on
    2018-12-22.

DESCRIPTION
    Modules that observe environment variable (other than NO_COLOR/COLOR) to
    disable/enable colored output.

    This is a list of modules that observe some environment variable to
    disable/enable colored output, but does not follow either the NO_COLOR
    convention or the COLOR convention.

    If you know of other modules that should be listed here, please contact
    me.

INCLUDED MODULES
    *   Term::ANSIColor

HOMEPAGE
    Please visit the project's homepage at
    <https://metacpan.org/release/Acme-CPANModules-ColorEnv>.

SOURCE
